			>
			--"and sk aggro will keep going up like it does every expansion."<br><br>wth are you talking about ?<br><br>oow is the only expansion to offer a direct hate spell thats worth asting.<br><br>before that sk's were using level 15 snare and fear to keep agro.<br><br>lvl 69 draygun is the next closest thing, but lets not get carried away, its a 3% upgrade from  thule.<br><br>whats more we only have 1 terror on a 6 second recast that gives 1800 hate [yes we have the Ae too but with 30 sec recast its something most would save incase of adds.]<br><br>im still using snare for agro, iirc snare is around 1100 hate ?<br><br>there is now an 1800 hate ancient stun and 1600 hate regular stun correct ?<br><br><br>now dont get me wrong, i have no complaints about the *amount* of hate i can generate, but due to most stuns casting in 1 second [correct me if im wrong] paladins have more hate for the first 9 secnds now no ? [providing they have oow ancient, which starts dropping on king/queen in rss]<br><br>i wish terror and snare cast in 1 second.<br><br><br><br><br>---"when SoE DID make them full strength Warriors with pocket Clerics"<br><br>when was this? all the knights and raid leaders must have missed the memmo, cause i swear warriors are still used to tank the hardest content.<br><br>oh thats right, your full of it, almost forgot.<br><br><br><br>---"I didn't want to be a Cleric with a Sword and I knew that's what the Paladin class was entitled to be"<br>---"The proper fix was adding Paladin aggro weapons, adding an aggro weapon buff spell, giving Paladins access to EoA on an item"<br><br>so why, exactly, should paladins need to use melee/proc based agro again?<br><br>i dont recall clerics ever getting agro from melee.<br>infact iirc clerics  are a spell based class no?<br><br>oh thats right, your full of it, almost forgot. <br><br><br>---"You didn't lose aggro to an overnuking Enchanter"<br><br>cant speak for paladins, but yesterday we did an MPG raid trial, i was one of the tanks assigned to keep agro on one of the mothers, nps, i've done it before.<br><br>i got agro, case 3 terrors, the rogue went up behind the mob and started whacking away.<br>at this point i have draygun up aswell [since i like the hp and it all helps] so every terror is making 2070 hate.<br>now the rogue didnt take agro, but i kept chaining terror so as to have a nice hate buffer when the pups spawned, i cast 24 terrors [i have the log] then the wizard takes agro, so i am infact forced to keep casting terror every time it pops.<br><br>the point is, 1. there are other classes who at equal progression to out-do my hate if i stop chain casting, 2. knights are designed for ranged hate, 3. stop whining about what paladins have, they arn't getting nerfed and SOE isn't going to suddenly give warriors equal hate to paladins, as you so like to point out, in the past warriors have never had equal hate, not even when verant was running the show and they arnt getting it now.<br>im all for lowering the END costs on bazu .etc [or even some sort of END regen AAs to compensate much like i need mana regen]or some such other solution to allow warriors to have enough hate and END for a chain pulling EXP group but your constant whining isn't going to endear enyone to your cause.<br>oh and lay off the crack, no one believes your bs [as quoted above] "paladins are clerics with sowrds ....paladins should need melee agro !" and in other posts "why should i have to hit bash for agro" "we should have something to replae the agro lost with sword and board"<br><br>waaa waaa waaa waaa.<br><br>next time you want to claim paladins are "full blown warriors with pocket clerics" bring several hours of parses to show how paladins have exactly the same melee mitigation and avoidance aswell as the patch notes where they got 3 mins of -45% DI mitigation disc as well as 12+ seconds of melee avoidance and some form of "on tap" AE agro.<br><br><br>talk about dishonest.
