		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Maddar_Xegony wrote:<BR>The overwhelming advantage you speak of isn't there Battleblade, care to try providing evidence?<BR><BR>And of course we were going to protest our epic click going from 120% to 20%. The effect, which although effective and unique was never all that overpowering to begin with (proven by the testimonies and research done by many paladins, who no, were not part of a massive class conspiracy), and was put in very much as it was intended. You don't make a silly coding error like that and get it through any kind of debugging phase of developement, period. What really happened, was that warriors were jelous of an effect they didn't understand, whined, and got it nerfed, end of story.<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Maddar, it was in fact a coding error. The text on the effect itself pretty well makes that evident. We were told from the onset that it was an error. I agree that it really wasn't as powerful as some claimed, however it was still too powerful, yes silly coding errors are made and succede in going through testing, debugging etc.</P>
<P>You are right that the contention by most Paladins (save a few, most of whom didn't fully understand the issue) was that 20% was much too small. This is why it took so long to change, simply correcting 120% to 20% could be done in mear minutes and by the first available patch, the debate was about what exactly was a propper effect.</P>
<P>The overwhelming advantage for Paladins is not there. I see nothing for Paladin aggro that couldn't be done and done better&nbsp;by any Shadow Knight, even without an Ancient spell. a 1400 spell and an 1800 hate spell on 13 sec recycles vs a 1800 hate on a 7 sec recycle. This is only for Paladins who have their ancient stun. A normal Paladin has a 1400 and a 1200 (max) on 13sec recycles vs that 1800 on a 7 sec cycle.</P>
<P>The issue here has nothing to do with Paladins. Sks did not, do not&nbsp;need to regear themselves, do not need to get better aggro weapons, aggro procs etc in order to get their Hate, Do not have Aggro issues, nothing mentioned by Warriors about Sks, nothing for what a year of their aggro being superior? But Paladins have a Aggro issue and it's "you need to replace your weapons not fix your spells" no Warrior cry at the begining of OoW that SKs shouldn't have gotten their Terror upgrade, no cry since then for a SK aggro Nerf, but god forbid if Paladins get any aggro upgrade whatsoever.</P>
<P>The Warrior issue is entirely that they have inadequate tools that need fixing. Stun aggro changes do not change anything for Warriors. It does demonstrate the needs of Warriors in the low end and low end SK Terror spells, but Paladin aggro is not the issue. <BR></P>
