			Jazzy,<br><br>Read what Paladins have written here and in the aggro threads on their board. It's all very consistant. They want fast repeat (without having to spam - BUT with the ability to spam if they wish), fast retargetable, ranged snap aggro (snap aggro = a lot of up front aggro) that allows them long term aggro competing with the aggro Warriors generate in the long term.<br><br>Aggro that does not require aggro discipline by other party members, capable of pulling aggro off an overnuking Wizard.<br><br>While turning their noses up at equipment that would improve their aggro output, freeing them from a substantial burden that is imposed on Warriors and giving them instead opprotunity to use group heal procs, non-aggro weapon buffs, in many cases non-aggro augs, benficial focus effects on their equipment, fuller benefit from shield use, and the ability to employ any weapon they wish while tanking.<br><br>The funny part, that's how overpowered their aggro has been for a very long time. Many don't ackowledge that in content where mobs are stunable, they enjoy a substantial benefit from stun avoidance. They call such content trivial, not understanding that it is their stuns that is making it trivial. They actualy lament that there are mobs they can not trivialize with stuns.<br><br>They have had godmode for so long, they believe they are entitled to god mode. In fact, if there is a drop off in any of this capability whatsoever they expect SoE to restore them to godmode without them needing to take on any of the equipment burdens imposed on Warriors. Such requirements would deprive tham of oprotunity where we have only burden.<br><br>I believe having asked repeatedly for the benefits of pure class specialization - defensive discs and abilities, always having a second attack, having no content where their less than 100% Warriorness makes it difficult to survive, etc. - they have to give up some of the perks of hybridization allowing them to ignore all of the burdens imposed on pure class specialists and seeing only lollipops and rainbows.<br><br>Translation - some Knights, partiularly Paladins, are unbelievably greedy. Suggest giving Warirors a fast refresh low mana/endurance fast retargetable aggro tools and doubltless they would complain. "Bbbbut we're supposed to be the undisputed Kings of Aggro!!!" (and of res, buffing, healing, stunning mobs, DPS vs. Undead, etc., etc., etc.).<br><br>Suggest putting Knight ratio 1Hdrs in the hands of Warriors for use with a shield and they freak out. "You'll do more damage than we do, you have triple attack!!" Guess what Sir Greedbucket, Warriors are SUPPOSED to do more melee damage than you, with ANY weapon we can both weild, and under ALL circumstances. You res, buff and heal better than we do.<br><br>Creating a Shieldmate weapon type, adding Warrior to the classes that can use BoD, and adding Knight ratio Shjieldmate weapons is a pretty modest request especially as it only partialy addresses Warrior shield use issues. It would also require Warriors to obtain addtional weapons - an equipment aquisition burden some Knights find so extreme, they won't do it to improve their own aggro - they believe they uniquely should be exempt from such things.<p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>12-01-2005</span> <span class=time_text>12:20 AM</span>	
