		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
JazzyJoyce wrote:<BR>
<DIV>One thing that keeps coming up that I have a problem with, it really bugs me. I'm not picking a fight, or picking on anyone. I just need to understand comment's like this.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"We wanted sufficient aggro so people wouldnt drag mobs off us when we were stunned, or by getting on a mob before we got to it after stunning it. That was a very common occurance, <FONT color=#ffff00>we stun a mob, it charges us, rogue or monk or wizard hits it before it gets to us, it turns on them.</FONT> That showed a deterioration in high end snap aggro for paladins that just about anybody could steal aggro from us after one stun, without trying. Course all we needed was a change from our normal aggro to our stuns being override aggro to fix that, but that wasnt what happened."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now, the reason this get's me, is it show's a "tank class" wanting Ranged aggro, without ever laying a hand on the mob. This in itself is already a given, and is very powerfull. In other words, knight's do have ranged aggro that works.... The highlighted part is what bugs me most. Not only do you want Range aggro, you want it unconditionally. One stun is supposed to give the Pally, unconditional aggro,&nbsp;even when&nbsp;the best DPS mellee in game, or the best Nuker in game hit's it or not... BEFORE the Pally is even in mellee range. Why should one stun out aggro a 5k nuke? Why should one stun out aggro a Rogue's DPS? I have to fight with class's like that all the time, to hold them back a GOOD while before going all out, and even then sometimes it's not enough. To be able to hold aggro with just one ALMIGHTY STUN seems way tooooooo powerfull. Even if the mob makes it to you before you get the second stun in, and stun's you in return, that should effect who the mob goes too. You shouldn't be able to keep aggro under that condition of bassically doing nothing at all, but............spinning? lol.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm going to go way out of my league's here and say, what your needing is taunt to work. I'm also going to aggree with a few other's about getting some aug's that produce hate/aggro as&nbsp;&nbsp; a&nbsp;&nbsp; "fast fix" untill taunt get's fixed. I am not a fan of Aug's and the like, but I do what I must to do my job, which part of it, and a big part of it is Aggro. I'm with you when talking about having trouble sustaining aggro over time, but wanting complete control of aggro with one stun sounds a bit, well, much. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Whenever a warrior tanks, we ussually make it a rule to let that warrior engage the mob fully before anyone starts nuking, Backstabbing, etc... Let the warrior get on it. Is it too much to ask your group to wait till you get your second stun off before they attack? </DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>Jazzy, The highlighted part is unreasonable, paladins hit stun and it turns to them (assume this is true if untouched) - they get initial agro which I think Frodlin says is capped at around 300?? not the full bore 1400 or1800 generated by a stun, thus anyone hitting and geting more than 300 hate will attract attention of the mob. Paladins who dont understand this realy need to figure it out and cast another stun that will do the full 1400 or 1800 - once they understand the initial agro settings then perhaps they will not need to ask for what as you say is unreasonable and what I concur is unreasonable too.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The above has got absolutely nothing to do with augging their weapons - another good piece of advice. The denialists here will say that we didnt need any upgrade to our agro and quite frankly they are wrong. They assert the reasons paladins asked for the stuff because they have believe in what they say - what they say is still wrong and was recognised as a problem and the developers addressed the problem in a way that has given us immediate relief from the problem - but the problem will arise again in the future as our agro is now static. I dearly hope that the EoA belt is a one off item like the VT gloves and the symbol of plainsmaker as like other paladins here I do want snap agro (front loaded) but with consequences i.e. that our long term agro is noticeably worse than warriors (but still adequate for grouping purposes). You need to put this front loading agro in context - on a raid (with 53 others around you) a warrior and a SK can obtain attention from multiple mobs on incoming - paladins has no method to do this - none - so we need to be able to peel them off the SKs or warriors and that can be done either taunt (which needs to be fixed) or by front loaded agro - Paladins as long as I have been in the game (which granted is not as long as the old timers here - but still with 4 year vet AAs and another due in April) have always had this at range agro and what has been granted by this recent agro improvement a return to the range agro - it needs to be reasonable and we will argue with what is reasonable in a reasonable way or some in an unreasonable way.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The EoA belt - we are engaging the mob that drops it and I will get it - but unlike others I suspect I will only use it when I am in tank mode as the belt that I currently has provides a plethera of modifications which I value higher than the mods on the belt. I hardly ever use my Boff - I use it only on mobs that I know produces a large amount of AE that my group heals wont surfice on. Yes I agree with BBx on this paladins are not immune from doing all they can to get themselves kitted out - I disagree that VT gloves and Symbol of Plainsmaster are reasonable for end game paladins to get just to maintain agro. I do wish that like weapon bandoliers that they would introduce armour bandoliers so that I have one for tanking and one for DPSing as a lot of the upgrades now will grant me&nbsp;better tanking abilities but lose modifications such as&nbsp;strikethrough&nbsp;or accuracy upgrades.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
