		" 
			>
			Someone wrote noting that Shildmate weapon wouldn't solve the aggro half of the Warrior/Shiled problem. Too true. They suggested adding Warrior only shield bash aggro generation. There are other alternative, including:<br><br>1. Redoing the Warrior Shield Block ability to modify the procrate mod of weapons wielded with a shield or modifying it to provide an aggro multiplier like EoA but more powerful automatically when a Warrior is using a shield.<br><br>2. Or providing a Mock-like ability for at-will pure hate generation.<br><br>In either case, the frequency and randomness of Warrior aggro events should be examined.<br><br>"Do not have Aggro issues, nothing mentioned by Warriors about Sks, nothing for what a year of their aggro being superior?"<br><br>There are a couple of things in operation here. Before the Provoke line was added, Warriors did in fact call attention to SK as well as Paladin aggro superiority and the consequences of it for Warriors. By and large SK's did not mount a multi-year campaign to acquire defensive discs or abilities, did not lobby to keep a 120% healing benefit on their epic, did not downplay the tremendous advantages of stun avoidance, etc. Like it or not, godmode seeking Paladins posting in your forum here and previously on PoN affect the perceptions about all Paladins.<br><br>I had a Pally tonight mention how much he is repelled by some of their campaigns and bogus claims. A Warrior replied that almost no one posts their disapproval - silence is taken as aggrement. There are some,like Bruennor, that will post outside of the party line, but they are shouted down, insulted, called trolls, etc.<br><br>Ice Vampire wrote:<br>"...a warrior and a SK can obtain attention from multiple mobs on incoming..."<br>On raids I use this capability very sparingly. On rare ocassions it's powerful. But on a mob after mob after mob basis, doing bread and butter clearing they are so useless as to not be worth mentioning compared to heavily front-loaded snap aggro. While I realize you are trying to be thoughful in this post,the ability of any tank to target a mob, obtain, and hold aggro for the 10 seconds needed to kill it and then immediately do it again with another mob should not dramatically outclass the other classes that tank.<br><br>The fact I have some ae aggro tools does not entitle Paladins to vastly superior short term aggro. Enough superiority to give them preference as add tanks? Sure thing. But Warriors have this Class Description that says "Warriors also learn to taunt their opponents, making themselves the focus of all their enemies' attacks, allowing the less resilient members of their group to remain safe from harm." I'm entitled to sufficient aggro tools so as to keep other more fragile players safe from harm too, even in the short term - on any mob I target so long as I have endurance and you have mana.	
