			>
			BruennorB wrote:<br>"A few questions for you battleblade. Do you think a paladin will keep chaining 3 stuns just for the heck of it?"<br><br>There are degrees of aggro adequacy.<br><br>Yes, I believe Paladins will in fact pile on the aggro early on allowing Wizards, Monks, and Rogues to unload right from the start where Warriors can not. This is little different from the early at range aggro abilities of Knights pre-Provoke line. Shaman could slow on incoming given the VERY solid dependable aggro both Knight classes could establish. In contrast, groups had to wait for Warriors to "establish" aggro before tashing, slowing,nuking, etc. A burden groups and raids are not likely to accept (and in fact didn't) if there is an alternative.<br><br>I also believe when taunt is fixed, a Paladin will be able to taunt spam stuns and not only not lose aggro inadvertanly to Warriors but be in a position to decide if they will ALLOW a Warrior to tank a mob. Do you honestly think the godmode seeking Paladins won't abuse excess capaility? I don't. I KNOW in fact some of them were raid MTing inappropriate mobs because they were long time members of guilds with huge DKP leads, better, equipment, and the ability to name who would MT. And let's not kid ourselves - a fair amount of the complaints were based on the fact that Warrior long term aggro was superior. Why, might I ask, would a Paladin care about how robust Warrior aggro is at the three minute mark?<br><br>"You werent made worse by our aggro being fixed, so whats the big deal?"<br>We were in fact made worse with the way your aggro was fixed. Those Paladins lusting to raid MT are a little closer.<br><br>Those believing since Warriors raid MT Paladins should dominate non-boss mob tanking have a way to ENFORCE their choice on who should tank adds.<br><br>With Paladins able to do a bucket load more aggro AND have a 20% aggro multiplier as well, they will be tanks of choice by those that want to unload and not control their aggro.<br><br>You got a FREE RIDE on aggro equipment - I can't even begin to list how much DKP I've spent on aggro in addition to non-aggro gear that Paladins are exempt from spending on.<br><br>Becuase of snap aggro, Paladins are the Class that can protect the frailer members of their party despite that role being explicitly assigned to Warriors in our Class Descriptions and not even mentioned in the Paladin Decription. Nice of you to co-op yet another Warrior role and pretend not only that you were entitled, but Warriors are supposed to be your inferiors at it.<br><br>I personally saw Paladins addtank Hanvar's adds, plowtank, etc. in Tacvi, Anguish, etc. WITHOUT continuously spamming stuns. They were a tossup with SK's as my guilds prefered addtanks sir. I assure you it would not assign tanks to perform roles they could not. The "issue" was bogus. And the "fix" was a FREE RIDE give away.<br><br>As I said before, a proper fix was adding aggro weapons, augs, a spell aggro weapon buff if getting SotP and Aten's gloves were too much of a burden, EoA on a piece of gear and scaling aggro from stuns including fizzling stuns that are too low in level to possibly do anything like Cease and Desist. Increasing the aggro on all stuns from FoP onward AND then giving you access to EoA was vast overkill exempting you from needing to account for aggro when obtaining equipment.<br><br>Yet again SoE comes to the beck and call of Paladins when Warrior aggro and taunt issues faced years of denial and neglect - and still do.<p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>12-01-2005</span> <span class=time_text>03:58 AM</span>	
