		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			First off, if I have a group getting owned by 5 mobs, I have no reliable way to get aggro on all 5 save by group heals, and the few times I have been in that situation, I have only gotten 2 or 3 of hte mobs on me, and had to stand and watch a few of my group members die before we evac'd, I died, or let a chanter get things under control if we have one.  You can ae taunt and go riposte or void disc.  So yes, you do the save the group job better.  Btw, our definition says we help our comrades =P, so it isnt necessarily just your job.<br><br>As for paladin aggro causing paladins to become boss tanks, I seriously doubt that.  First off sk's have life taps which cause aggro while healing.  They can ac tap, hp tap, and toss dots and more on to keep aggro mounting up.  So why you seem to fear pally stuns, you are at just as much of a risk from sk's to.  Sk's have had their ability to create insane aggro for a while now, and warriors still tank the big time, so I feel that your fear of paladins stealing boss mob tanking across the board is unfounded.  In situations where paladins do tank boss content, sadly a majority of that is just old content.<br><br>You mention the demi plane of blood pally belt with eoa 4.  This is one of the few times you have shown interest in actual high end paladin concerns.  You do understand that you have to be in a kick ass guild to get that belt correct?  You are fighting stuff that knights cant main tank, boss wise.  You are basically showing concern over an item that doesnt hurt any warriors in any way unless a paladin, fully decked in anguish+ gear, and wearing that belt quits the guild he was in and joins a lower end guild and tanks bosses with that belt on.  Course, you can see how silly that sounds.  It can happen, but so few paladins have the belt available to them, and only a slim percentage of the few percent that have access to the belt will leave their guild for a guild raiding time, or similiar content.<br><br>I believe when taunt is fixed, warriors will be taunt kings, knights will be a definite second.  I feel that soe will concentrate on making taunt more useful for you than for us.  Course, this is my opinion, so we will just have to see how it goes.<br><br>You always ignore all the gear a paladin has to get to be considered correctly geared.  We dont have to get hate proc weapons, but we do have to get tanking mods, and smart knights get stun resist, plus half our focii are required to be useful, the other are optional, but important to knights none the less.  To date I still dont have a cleave or fero item, because I focus on healing and tanking, dps isnt part of my make up.  You can concentrate on tanking and dps.  So you concentrate on tanking and dps, I concentrate on tanking, dps, and healing, so who has more gear they have to get to remain competetive in their class?  Plus, if I want to be completely useful in all ways, I need nuke focii to, even though I only have a undead nuke.  Well, I got a 125 point live nuke.....<br><br>As for hanvar, my guild does it this way.  First, one main assist, then all other tanks snag initial targets.  Raid assists main assist, and they plow each mob.  So no, you dont see paladins spam stun on those, as they are expecting to lose aggro to the MA so they can go add hunting again.<br><br>Plow tanking in anguish, txevu, and what not is a full raid thing for my guild.  For some reasons, we even have shaman's and other non tank classes run ahead so they can get a mob to play with till the raid gets there.  Before a cleric in our guild retired, he used to run ahead of the raid and pronounce himself cleradin, and try to tank 2 to 3 mobs at a time.  Course, this left him dead half the time.  Point is, anybody can plow tank.  Not in tacvi though.  As a knight, you need top of the top gear and insane dps to live through most of hte mastrugs, and there is almost no chance of a paladin living through the flurry mastrug.  Course, I could be wrong, since my guild has never wasted the time trying to tank mastrugs with knights.  We use fully geared main tanks, and even less stats than my pally, app warriors when we have one.  Shame they seem to die so much though.<br><br>I will never agree with you on giving knights aggro weapons.  We arent warriors, we are knights.  Your gig is aggro weapons, ours is aggro spells.  This is the way it has always been since paladins used flash of light, to using the stuns of today.  You find a reasonable spell fix, then I am game to discuss, but anything having to do with requiring itemization, and rearranging eq completely, and making it require something it didnt require before..... no, I wont agree with that.<p>Message Edited by BruennorB on <span class=date_text>12-01-2005</span> <span class=time_text>07:25 AM</span>	
