		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			"First off sk's have life taps which cause aggro while healing. They can ac tap, hp tap, and toss dots and more on to keep aggro mounting up. So why you seem to fear pally stuns, you are at just as much of a risk from sk's to. Sk's have had their ability to create insane aggro for a while now, and warriors still tank the big time, so I feel that your fear of paladins stealing boss mob tanking across the board is unfounded."<br><br>Lifetaps are not used for aggro.  The amount of aggro generated is relatively small.  If you're relying on taps to build aggro, you won't keep it long.  We simply don't use taps while tanking anything until solid aggro has been created.  That means before a mob is debuffed, we're not tapping, we're not ac tapping, we're generally just aggroing.  On the point that SK's have the ability to create insane aggro, pally single target aggro is really pretty similar to ours now, and has the added benifit of casting faster and stunning some mobs.<br><br>"I will never agree with you on giving knights aggro weapons. We arent warriors, we are knights."<br><br>I'd quite frankly love to be itemized a couple of high aggro knight weapons.  We will never generate as much aggro from procs as warriors, but I think once we've generated sufficient spell aggro, it's reasonable to expect our melee/proc aggro to "maintain" our aggro over the course of a fight, at least in exp groups... boss fights you'll likely require more sustained aggro than a single proccing weapon could generate.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
