<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
BruennorB wrote:<BR>I know your life taps arent used for aggro Josahd, I added it in that list because somebody would of inevitably brought up the fact that paladins can self heal, and I am showing them that we share many things, and even though you have the aggro we have, and more over time, you havent replaced warriors in all area's of play in EQ.<BR><BR>I wouldnt mind an aggro weapon as long as it has 2 effects, the normal knight ones and a aggro proc. If its just one proc, I prefer to use a weapon that actually helps me when raiding vs something that I can only use when not casting, which means barely ever, since I have to chain cast on raid trash clearing. The paladin specific weapons usually feature procs that help a group out in ae situations, plus have decent tank stats. <FONT color=#ffff00>I already go for a 2hander and a 1h/shield selection, I dont think it would be fair to force aggro fixes through itemization on the knight class when it has never been done before, and has no reason to be done.<BR></FONT><BR>Also, oops. Didnt notice Ice didnt mention that the hate over ride already went live =x Aye, paladin aggro is good now, our snap aggro works, as does the ability to not have to chain cast non stop in groups.
<P>Message Edited by BruennorB on <SPAN class=date_text>12-01-2005</SPAN> <SPAN class=time_text>09:44 AM</SPAN><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>I might be wrong, but the introduction to aggro/hate aug's for warrior's was supposed to be a quick fix, but not a true fix to the aggro/hate problems they faced in POP? It's a question not a statement of fact:-)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>From what I understand, is your talking about the high end. I would consider that reason enough to at least consider some other options, outside of stun's. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>From my experience's with Knight's, Pally's has always won the initial aggro war, even with SK's. SK's are faster then warrior's, and seem to even rival warrior's on long term aggro, but far as a mob coming to group, and running to the tank immediately... it's alway's seemed to be the Pally. I'm sure "Summoning" mobs have something to do with it, however, it has something to do with almost all class's, when facing summoning mobs. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"I wouldnt mind an aggro weapon as long as it has 2 effects, the normal knight ones and a aggro proc. If its just one proc, I prefer to use a weapon that actually helps me when raiding vs something that I can only use when not casting, which means barely ever, since I have to chain cast on raid trash clearing. The paladin specific weapons usually feature procs that help a group out in ae situations, plus have decent tank stats." </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm not exactly sure what you mean here.... My question to you is, Don't you think a Warrior would like to be able to put in some fancy aug's that help/heal/etc a group as well? We sacrifise certain fancie's, in favor of what is needed to get the job done. Something was said that Pally's have to get tanking, DPS, and&nbsp;focus type aug's/effects, where warrior's just need tanking and DPS, although aggro is a very big part of that as well. See, we don't just use one for this&nbsp;and&nbsp;one for that (or at least I don't practice it that way). I use all available options for aggro/hate, if there is two slots in my&nbsp;weapon for aug's, I&nbsp;would want nothing but aggro&nbsp;inducing augment's in them. It's not a choice, as most warrior's still need help in that area, even after doing everything possible to get aggro. IF we had adequate aggro with just one slot, then the other's&nbsp;could be used for "funner" type effects, which could include a number of things, and would be alot more benificial...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Bassically, what&nbsp;I'm trying to say&nbsp;is : If a Warrior were to take the same stance, in what they felt should be "Required" for aggro, one might claim that they should never need more then one dedicated slot, for aggro. Then we could say, we need the other slot's for more usefull group effects, stuff that helps us out. We simply can't afford to give up a slot that an aggro effect can be put into. If I wanted aggro, and felt I was inadequate with what I have (even if I was not a Warrior), I would try other things out as well. IF the augments/items were supposed to only be used by warrior's, they would have a Warrior only stamp on them. My son (who has a 63 SK) put an aug on his BOD, first thing after getting the blade. He never felt that his spells should be solely what he counted on for aggro. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I just feel, that hitting a stun here and there to insure aggro, isn't really that much of&nbsp;a hassle. We get proc's that do the same, to try and stay on top. The only way we are going to get more hate then a pally, even over time, is if that pally just stops stunning. Two stuns initially,&nbsp; a third to keep it for a minute or so, and one every so often to keep your hate on top. To demand one end all to the problem is just a bit overpower'd. All tanks have problems with Rogue's and Wizzy's, if they are going all out. That's just a matter of aggro management, which can be managed by not nuking your best nuke everytime. I have a wizzy, I know what get's aggro, and what I can do to not get aggro. I tend to hold off my best nukes for the ends of fights, not the beggining.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If Pally's get a one shot spell that can hold aggro from a wizzy's best nuke on incoming, Then all tanks should be able to do that. I can understand the frustration of having one nuke ahead of time, but that should be talked about to the wizzy doing it, and not a reason to upgrade something that don't need it at that level of impact. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
