			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Battleblade-Xegony wrote:<BR>Jazzy,<BR><BR>Read what Paladins have written here and in the aggro threads on their board. It's all very consistant. They want fast repeat (without having to spam - BUT with the ability to spam if they wish), fast retargetable, ranged snap aggro (snap aggro = a lot of up front aggro) that allows them long term aggro competing with the aggro Warriors generate in the long term.<BR><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>No Battleblade, despite your propoganda, that isn't what Paladins wanted at all. What we wanted was scaled aggro on our stuns, which were aggro capped (ie Paladins didn't get an aggro upgrade after 65, do you&nbsp;have Bezu? do SKs&nbsp;have the new Terror?" This capping of aggro and lack of scaled aggro was causing the need to spam stuns excessively.</P>
<P>What was generally proposed and agreed upon in those threads was that Stun Aggro should scale to spell level, with the higher end Stuns generating more aggro and the lower level stuns generating less.</P>
<P>This wouldn't give us any more ability for "fast repeat" aggro then SKs already have, in fact we have less. Terror recycles 1800 hate every 7 seconds. Our top 2 stuns would recycle every 6.5 seconds combined, but with 400 less Hate then the SKs in the same time frame. If our lower level spells were reduced AS PALADINS INSISTED WOULD BE NEEDED, then <EM>"the ability to spam if they wish" </EM>would produce no greater results then we would already be capible of doing before the change. As the thrid stun would produce LESS aggro then it currently does. Again this is even less then what SKs can do if they chain their Terror spell with Snares and the such inbetween and would be less Long term aggro then Warriors. Also as pointed out in those threads, this could also be used to balance out aggro in the lower end where Paladins are extremely strong, by setting the hate values of lower end stuns to appropriate levels (hey yea, Paladins asking for an aggro nerf?) which is an issue for Warriors.</P>
<P>Battleblade, the problem with opening a discussion with you is that your a walking talking propoganda machine who isn't interested in making a propper arguement but simply in insisting on rehashing old material. What solutions that Paladins looked for in early GoD or what we suggested we needed 2, 3 or 4 expansions, or what we thought about Warrior aggro problems in LDoN is completely not relevant to today's game. Paladin says, "we have aggro issues with Stun aggro not scaling" and your reply is "OMG!! YOU WANTED WARRIOR DEFENSIVE 2 YEARS AGO!"</P>
<P>Despite that, you'll find that&nbsp;most Paladins wholey agree with Warrior 1-Handers for shields with knight ratios. Hell I suggested them myself when the shield block issue first came out, I do beleive you shot me down and insisted that Warrior's shouldn't need to get new weapons to use shields and went on some anti-paladin rant...<BR></P>
